hopobject.body: Can you put it on the scales, please? vahard cvs In the "Star Wars" film trilogy, Luke Skywalker's home planet of Tatooine featured a double sunset, something that scientists doubted could ever happen, Batalha said. Orbiting two stars would be difficult; the planet would be pulled by so many gravitational forces, she explained. But Kepler found it. Kepler-16b is one of the planets the telescope identified as orbiting two stars -- now nicknamed "Tatooine" for the planet in George Lucas' film. And there may be more. Kepler found 2,165 pairs of stars orbiting each other in its survey so far.
